        {
            "data": {
                "is_heading": 1,
                "prefix": 1.0,
                "text": "Introduction"
            },
            "type": "ListItem",
            "sequence_num": 18
        },
        {
            "data": {
                "is_heading": 0,
                "prefix": 1.1,
                "text": "To ensure standardisation of AM and PM board rounds."
            },
            "type": "ListItem",
            "sequence_num": 19
        },
        {
            "data": {
                "is_heading": 0,
                "prefix": 1.2,
                "text": "To provide reassurance of expectations of members of the MDT."
            },
            "type": "ListItem",
            "sequence_num": 20
        },
        {
            "data": {
                "is_heading": 0,
                "prefix": 1.3,
                "text": "Positively impacts upon the reduction in Length of Stay (LoS) and a decrease in the amount of stranded patients."
            },
            "type": "ListItem",
            "sequence_num": 21
        },
        {
            "data": {
                "is_heading": 1,
                "prefix": 2.0,
                "text": "Scope"
            },
            "type": "ListItem",
            "sequence_num": 22
        },
        {
            "data": {
                "is_heading": 0,
                "prefix": 2.1,
                "text": "The purpose of this document is to:"
            },
            "type": "ListItem",
            "sequence_num": 23
        },
        {
            "data": {
                "is_heading": 0,
                "text": "This document is applicable across all inpatient ward areas across MSE required to complete AM & PM board rounds."
            },
            "type": "ListItem",
            "sequence_num": 24
        },
        {
            "data": {
                "is_heading": 1,
                "prefix": 3.0,
                "text": "Definitions"
            },
            "type": "ListItem",
            "sequence_num": 25
        },
        {
            "type": "table",
            "sequence_num": 26,
            "data": {
                "num_rows": 4,
                "num_cols": 2,
                "table_items": [
                    {
                        "text": "TERM"
                    },
                    {
                        "text": "DEFINITION"
                    },
                    {
                        "text": "LoS"
                    },
                    {
                        "text": "Length of Stay"
                    },
                    {
                        "text": "MDT"
                    },
                    {
                        "text": "Multidisciplinary Team"
                    },
                    {
                        "text": "EDD"
                    },
                    {
                        "text": "Expected Date of Discharge"
                    }
                ]
            }
        },
        {
            "data": {
                "is_heading": 1,
                "prefix": 4.0,
                "text": "Role and responsibilities within the Trust"
            },
            "type": "ListItem",
            "sequence_num": 27
        },
        {
            "data": {
                "is_heading": 1,
                "prefix": 4.1,
                "text": "Clinical or Divisional Director"
            },
            "type": "ListItem",
            "sequence_num": 28
        },
        {
            "data": {
                "is_heading": 0,
                "text": "It is the responsibility of the Clinical or Divisional Director to ensure compliance amongst the medical teams for expectations outlined in this document."
            },
            "type": "ListItem",
            "sequence_num": 29
        },
        {
            "data": {
                "is_heading": 1,
                "prefix": 4.2,
                "text": "Director of Nursing"
            },
            "type": "ListItem",
            "sequence_num": 30
        },
        {
            "data": {
                "is_heading": 0,
                "text": "It is the responsibility of the Director of Nursing to ensure board rounds are firmly in place within their areas of responsibility and that appropriate action is taken when expectations within this document are not complied with."
            },
            "type": "ListItem",
            "sequence_num": 31
        },
        {
            "data": {
                "is_heading": 1,
                "prefix": 4.3,
                "text": "Matrons"
            },
            "type": "ListItem",
            "sequence_num": 32
        },
        {
            "data": {
                "is_heading": 0,
                "text": "Matrons are responsible for providing reassurance that AM and PM board rounds are firmly in place and well attended within their clinical areas. It is their responsibility to escalate where expectations within this document are not complied with."
            },
            "type": "ListItem",
            "sequence_num": 33
        },
        {
            "data": {
                "is_heading": 1,
                "prefix": 4.4,
                "text": "Medical Teams"
            },
            "type": "ListItem",
            "sequence_num": 34
        },
        {
            "data": {
                "is_heading": 0,
                "text": "It is the medical teams responsibility to ensure they attend both AM and PM board rounds. It is the expectation that the Consultant must attend the AM board round however may delegate the PM board round to a senior decision maker."
            },
            "type": "ListItem",
            "sequence_num": 35
        },
        {
            "data": {
                "is_heading": 1,
                "prefix": 4.5,
                "text": "Nursing Staff"
            },
            "type": "ListItem",
            "sequence_num": 36
        },
        {
            "data": {
                "is_heading": 0,
                "text": "At least 1 member of nursing team should attend AM and PM board rounds. Preferably this would be the nurse in charge."
            },
            "type": "ListItem",
            "sequence_num": 37
        },
        {
            "data": {
                "is_heading": 0,
                "text": "The Flow Coordinator should attend AM and PM board rounds."
            },
            "type": "ListItem",
            "sequence_num": 38
        },
        {
            "data": {
                "is_heading": 0,
                "text": "The board round should be led by either the consultant or the nurse in charge."
            },
            "type": "ListItem",
            "sequence_num": 39
        },
        {
            "data": {
                "is_heading": 0,
                "text": "The MDTs should review every expected date of discharge (EDD) on every board round. It is the responsibility of the nurse in charge to ensure that Tele tracking is updated throughout the day by the relevant team members of the team."
            },
            "type": "ListItem",
            "sequence_num": 40
        },
        {
            "data": {
                "is_heading": 1,
                "prefix": 4.6,
                "text": "Therapies"
            },
            "type": "ListItem",
            "sequence_num": 41
        },
        {
            "data": {
                "is_heading": 0,
                "text": "It is the responsibility of Therapy staff to attend board rounds twice daily and comply with the expectations of this document."
            },
            "type": "ListItem",
            "sequence_num": 42
        },
        {
            "data": {
                "is_heading": 1,
                "prefix": 4.7,
                "text": "Pharmacy"
            },
            "type": "ListItem",
            "sequence_num": 43
        },
        {
            "data": {
                "is_heading": 0,
                "text": "The ward Pharmacist/Technician should aim to attend the one of the board rounds and comply with the expectations of this document. If unable to attend they should liaise with the NIC at their earliest convenience to expedite discharge dependant medication/TTA"
            },
            "type": "ListItem",
            "sequence_num": 44
        },
        {
            "data": {
                "is_heading": 1,
                "prefix": 4.8,
                "text": "Complex discharge planning"
            },
            "type": "ListItem",
            "sequence_num": 45
        },
        {
            "data": {
                "is_heading": 0,
                "text": "The Flow Coordinator, or in their absence, the nurse in charge, should dial in to the Golden Hour Teams' meeting to discuss and escalate any tests, scans, specialty reviews for the medically fit patients and to get an update on all patients in the complex discharge process. These are held every weekday morning."
            },
            "type": "ListItem",
            "sequence_num": 46
        },
        {
            "data": {
                "is_heading": 1,
                "prefix": 5.0,
                "text": "Operational standards"
            },
            "type": "ListItem",
            "sequence_num": 47
        },
        {
            "data": {
                "is_heading": 1,
                "prefix": 5.1,
                "text": "AM: Board round process:"
            },
            "type": "ListItem",
            "sequence_num": 48
        },
        {
            "data": {
                "is_heading": 0,
                "text": "The board round should take no longer than 30 minutes."
            },
            "type": "ListItem",
            "sequence_num": 49
        },
        {
            "data": {
                "is_heading": 0,
                "text": "Each patient must be briefly discussed during every board round, with the following questions asked:"
            },
            "type": "ListItem",
            "sequence_num": 50
        },
        {
            "data": {
                "is_heading": 0,
                "text": "o  Is the patient responding to treatment as expected and is their care plan defined? If not, an urgent consultant review is essential and regular NEWS (National Early Warning Score) required."
            },
            "type": "ListItem",
            "sequence_num": 51
        },
        {
            "data": {
                "is_heading": 0,
                "text": "If new, has the patient had a consultant review?"
            },
            "type": "ListItem",
            "sequence_num": 52
        },
        {
            "data": {
                "is_heading": 0,
                "text": "Does the patient have an expected date of discharge and physiological and function criteria for discharge?"
            },
            "type": "ListItem",
            "sequence_num": 53
        },
        {
            "data": {
                "is_heading": 0,
                "text": "Is the patient to be discharged today? Are they ready to go? At what time will they leave the ward?"
            },
            "type": "ListItem",
            "sequence_num": 54
        },
        {
            "data": {
                "is_heading": 0,
                "text": "Is the patient to be discharged tomorrow? Is everything arranged?"
            },
            "type": "ListItem",
            "sequence_num": 55
        },
        {
            "data": {
                "is_heading": 0,
                "text": "Consider cannulas, catheters, VTE, skin integrity, pain, wounds."
            },
            "type": "ListItem",
            "sequence_num": 56
        },
        {
            "data": {
                "is_heading": 1,
                "text": "Establish team priorities for the day in this order \u2013 S-Sick patients, H-Home, O-P \u2013Other Patients (SHOP)."
            },
            "type": "ListItem",
            "sequence_num": 57
        },
        {
            "data": {
                "is_heading": 0,
                "text": "Actions must be documented and reviewed in the afternoon. The nurse in charge and Flow Co-ordinators are accountable for ensuring Tele Tracking is kept up to date throughout the day."
            },
            "type": "ListItem",
            "sequence_num": 58
        },
        {
            "data": {
                "is_heading": 0,
                "text": "Escalate delays in assessments and diagnostics at Golden hour or to Zonal Representative for the day or the Flow Hub."
            },
            "type": "ListItem",
            "sequence_num": 59
        },
        {
            "data": {
                "is_heading": 1,
                "prefix": 5.2,
                "text": "PM board rounds process: No more than 15 minutes"
            },
            "type": "ListItem",
            "sequence_num": 60
        },
        {
            "data": {
                "is_heading": 0,
                "text": "Board round can be led by a senior decision making doctor or consultant if unavailable."
            },
            "type": "ListItem",
            "sequence_num": 61
        },
        {
            "data": {
                "is_heading": 0,
                "text": "Board rounds must be multidisciplinary."
            },
            "type": "ListItem",
            "sequence_num": 62
        },
        {
            "data": {
                "is_heading": 0,
                "text": "All actions from the AM board round should be reviewed and all new actions assigned to one of the team."
            },
            "type": "ListItem",
            "sequence_num": 63
        },
        {
            "data": {
                "is_heading": 0,
                "text": "Confirmed and pending discharges should be identified and added to Tele tracking for the following day, especially those who can be discharged before midday (Home for lunch patient)."
            },
            "type": "ListItem",
            "sequence_num": 64
        },
        {
            "data": {
                "is_heading": 0,
                "text": "TTA and EDL should be completed for next day discharges."
            },
            "type": "ListItem",
            "sequence_num": 65
        },
        {
            "data": {
                "is_heading": 0,
                "text": "Where required, patients who are deemed suitable to outlie should be identified. This will exclude patients on an EOL pathway or those with Dementia or with impaired cognition. This is to ensure that when operational team requires specific additional capacity the most appropriate patients are not only identified but also moved before the evening."
            },
            "type": "ListItem",
            "sequence_num": 66
        },
        {
            "data": {
                "is_heading": 1,
                "prefix": 6.0,
                "text": "Training requirements"
            },
            "type": "ListItem",
            "sequence_num": 67
        },
        {
            "data": {
                "is_heading": 0,
                "prefix": 6.1,
                "text": "All appropriate staff should have training on use of Tele Tracking and SAFER patient flow bundle."
            },
            "type": "ListItem",
            "sequence_num": 68
        },
        {
            "data": {
                "is_heading": 1,
                "prefix": 7.0,
                "text": "Monitoring and audit"
            },
            "type": "ListItem",
            "sequence_num": 69
        },
        {
            "data": {
                "is_heading": 0,
                "prefix": 7.1,
                "text": "Outlined below is the Trust's process of monitoring compliance with, and the effectiveness of the document's main points."
            },
            "type": "ListItem",
            "sequence_num": 70
        },
        {
            "data": {
                "is_heading": 0,
                "prefix": 7.2,
                "text": "Auditing/Monitoring of Board Rounds will be used as a quality assurance procedure undertaken by either a clinician or senior nurse who is independent of and separate from the Board Round under review."
            },
            "type": "ListItem",
            "sequence_num": 71
        },
        {
            "data": {
                "is_heading": 0,
                "prefix": 7.3,
                "text": "The purpose of auditing/monitoring Board Rounds is to evaluate conduct and compliance with this Board Round standard operating procedure (SOP) and guidelines. The board round scorecard can be utilised for reviews (Appendix 2)"
            },
            "type": "ListItem",
            "sequence_num": 72
        },
        {
            "data": {
                "is_heading": 0,
                "prefix": 7.4,
                "text": "Audit/Monitoring visits may take place at any time (random peer reviews), although adequate notice could be given depending on the circumstances."
            },
            "type": "ListItem",
            "sequence_num": 73
        },
